## 📦 Installation

### 1. Clone repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/<your-username>/data-sentinel.git
cd data-sentinel

2. Create virtual environment
python -m venv .venv
.venv\Scripts\activate
3. Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt
4. Configure environment

Create .env file:

OPENAI_API_KEY=your_key_here
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:password@localhost:5432/datasentinel
5. Run backend
uvicorn backend.app.main:app --reload
Backend runs at:

http://127.0.0.1:8000

API docs:

http://127.0.0.1:8000/docs

### 6. Run frontend (Streamlit)
streamlit run frontend/dashboard.py

#Frontend runs at:

http://localhost:8501

🐳 Docker (Optional)
docker compose up -d

📡 API Endpoints
| Method | Endpoint               | Description                        |
| ------ | ---------------------- | ---------------------------------- |
| POST   | `/upload-csv`          | Upload dataset and generate report |
| GET    | `/reports`             | Get all stored reports             |
| GET    | `/reports/{id}`        | Get specific report                |
| GET    | `/reports/{id}/status` | AI processing status               |


🔐 Design Principles
AI layer is optional and non-blocking
System works fully without OpenAI API
NumPy types normalized before database storage
Background tasks handle AI processing asynchronously
Fail-safe design for quota / auth / API errors

📌 Roadmap
Advanced drift scoring (KL divergence / Jensen-Shannon)
Real-time streaming ingestion
Authentication system (JWT / OAuth2)
Dataset comparison UI (before vs after)
Scheduled data quality monitoring
Export reports (PDF / CSV)

